.TH "libnvme_transport_handle_set_submit_exit" 9 "libnvme_transport_handle_set_submit_exit" "April 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
libnvme_transport_handle_set_submit_exit \- Install a submit-exit callback
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" libnvme_transport_handle_set_submit_exit
.BI "(struct libnvme_transport_handle *hdl "  ","
.BI "void (*submit_exit)(struct libnvme_transport_handle *hdl, struct libnvme_passthru_cmd *cmd, int err, void *user_data) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hdl" 12
Transport handle to configure
.IP "submit_exit" 12
Callback invoked after a passthrough command completes. The
function receives the command, the completion status \fIerr\fP
(0 for success, a negative errno, or an NVMe status value), and
the \fIuser_data\fP pointer returned earlier by the submit-entry
callback. Implementations typically use this hook for logging,
tracing, or freeing per-command state.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Installs a callback that is invoked when a passthrough command leaves the
NVMe submission path. Passing NULL removes any previously installed callback.
.SH "RETURN"
None.
